President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Colorado due to wildfires and straight-line winds that occurred since December 30, 2021. This declaration allows federal funding to be provided to affected individuals in Boulder County. Assistance may include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in recovery. Federal funding is also available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures in Boulder County and statewide. Nancy M. Casper has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and more counties and forms of assistance may be designated in the future. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance starting tomorrow through the DisasterAssistance.gov website or by calling FEMA. The toll-free telephone numbers will be operational from 7 a.m. to 10 p.m. seven days a week. For more information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted.